&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Theatre / Pre-operative Assessment Clinic Coordinator for iMSK (B4)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time: 37.5 hours/week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;1 year fixed term contract/1 year secondment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to provide a key role in the effective operational delivery of the iMSK &amp; Trauma Service at Ashford and St Peter’s Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and highly motivated team player, who shows flexibility and careful attention to detail. Excellent administration skills are required, along with an exceptional telephone manner. The successful candidate will make best use of resources by making maximum use of available theatre and clinics slots, ensuring they are filled to the agreed capacity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role requires timely response to all telephone and email enquiries from patients and other agencies with regards to referrals and outpatient appointments, whilst providing patients with a high quality service. This will be done taking account of patients’ rights and diversity and ensuring that all patients receive equal opportunity to services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be required to use a number of computer systems including Bluespier, eRS, PAS, Patient Centre, Evolve, CRIS, Dictate I.T. and others. Previous experience of these systems is desirable, but not essential, as training will be provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Smita Shetty - Service Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;smita.shetty@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
